; Regression test for issue #1133: Erroneous double colon in account gives 'Unknown account' error listing only single colon with '--strict'. (BZ#1133)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1133
; The original bug: when an account with a double colon (e.g. Assets::Cash) was used
; with --strict, the error said "Unknown account 'Assets:Cash'" (single colon), making
; it hard to identify the erroneous entry. Now ledger correctly reports a parse error
; identifying the empty sub-account name.
account Assets:Cash
account Expenses:Food

2024/01/01 Test
    Assets::Cash    $10.00
    Expenses:Food

test --strict bal -> 1
__ERROR__
While parsing file "$FILE", line 11:
While parsing posting:
  Assets::Cash    $10.00

Error: Account name contains an empty sub-account name
end test
